        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 3:10AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 310 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Fredonia, or 8 miles northeast of De Valls Bluff, moving northeast at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cotton Plant...                   Hunter...
Dagmar WMA...                     Fredonia...
Fargo...                          Hilleman...
Brasfield...                      Zent...
Brinkley...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
